Package: ppcviz
Title: Diagnostics and Recommendations for Visual Predictive Checks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Study", "Implementation", email = "utkarshpawade2@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "Learning exercise; implements methodology from arXiv:2503.01509")
Description: A self-learning implementation of the methodology from Sailynoja,
    Johnson, Martin & Vehtari (2025) <arXiv:2503.01509> "Recommendations for
    visual predictive checks in Bayesian workflow". This package is a personal
    study exercise and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the original authors.
    It provides tools to (1) compute visualization PIT values that test whether a
    chosen plot type faithfully represents the data distribution, (2) run
    goodness-of-fit diagnostics for visualizations using simultaneous ECDF
    confidence bands, (3) detect data properties (discreteness, bounds, point
    masses), (4) produce PAVA-based calibration plots for binary and discrete
    outcomes, and (5) automatically recommend appropriate posterior predictive
    check plots.
